-- Corrected: Harley-Davidson profit, sales hit by strike
-- 
-- Thu Apr 19, 2007 7:32am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/04/19/us-harley-results-idUSWNAS681820070419

 

 (Corrects first-quarter profit in paragraph 2 to $192.3 million, or 74 cents a share) 

 CHICAGO  (Reuters) - Harley-Davidson Inc. ( HOG.N ) said on Thursday that earnings in the latest quarter fell as a strike a key plant idled production for nearly a month. The U.S. motorcycle maker reported a first-quarter profit of $192.3 million, or 74 cents a share, compared with $234.6 million, or 86 cents a share, last year. Sales fell 8.3 percent to $1.18 billion. Analysts, on average, expected the Milwaukee-based company to earn 72 cents a share on sales of $1.10 billion, according to Reuters Estimates.